## Architecture Guidance
{% if arch_type == "microservice" %}
- Do NOT reference entities from other services
- Use UUID for primary keys (distributed ID generation)
- Include soft delete (deleted_at) for data recovery
- Design for eventual consistency with other services
{% elif arch_type == "modular-monolith" %}
- Prefix tables with module name for namespace isolation
- Mark cross-module references explicitly
{% else %}
- Use foreign keys for referential integrity
- Design for the shared database context
{% endif %}

## Anti-Patterns

Do NOT:
- Generate placeholder field types like "[TBD]"
- Skip constraints (NOT NULL, UNIQUE, CHECK)
- Ignore indexing strategy
- Design entities without considering query patterns
- Reference entities from other services in a microservice architecture
